## Plan

### What changes and why

Two coordinated gates block drag-and-drop reordering while tasks are running:
1. **QueuePanel's `ReorderEnabled`** (line 57) checks `IsBusy == false`, so the drag gesture never initiates.
2. **ViewModel's `MoveTask`** (line 115) returns early when `IsBusy`, so even if a drag were initiated, the reorder would be silently dropped.

Both gates are unnecessarily conservative. The drain already snapshots its execution order at `RelayQueueController.DrainAsync:113` (`var queue = Tasks.ToList()`) from the controller's own collection — reordering the ViewModel's visible `Tasks` during a drain cannot affect in-flight execution. Single runs (`RunOneAsync`) track the running task by ID and don't iterate the Tasks collection. And `MoveTask` already persists every move via `TaskOrderStore.Save()` (Commands.cs:134), so a reorder made during a drain survives the post-drain `ReloadTaskListAsync` rebuild from disk.

The fix is to remove `IsBusy` from both reorder gates while leaving all other `IsBusy` guards intact (`CanRunSelected`, `CanDrain`, `CanMarkSelectedTaskDone`, etc. remain gated on `IsBusy` — only reorder is relaxed).

---

### Concrete changes

#### 1. `src/VisualRelay.App/Views/Controls/QueuePanel.axaml.cs` — line 57

Remove `IsBusy: false` from the `ReorderEnabled` property pattern match so drag can initiate during active runs:

```csharp
// Before (line 56-57):
private bool ReorderEnabled =>
    DataContext is MainWindowViewModel { IsBusy: false, ShowArchive: false };

// After:
private bool ReorderEnabled =>
    DataContext is MainWindowViewModel { ShowArchive: false };
```

This unlocks all three drag gates: `OnListPointerPressed` (line 61), `OnDragOver` (line 122), and implicitly `OnDrop` (which calls `MoveTask`).

#### 2. `src/VisualRelay.App/ViewModels/MainWindowViewModel.Commands.cs` — line 115

Remove `IsBusy` from `MoveTask`'s early-return guard:

```csharp
// Before (line 115):
if (IsBusy || ShowArchive)

// After:
if (ShowArchive)
```

This allows the ViewModel to actually perform the reorder when the drop handler calls `vm.MoveTask(from, to)` even while `IsBusy` is true.

#### 3. `tests/VisualRelay.Tests/MainWindowViewModelTests.Reorder.cs` — lines 149–159

Flip the existing `MoveTask_IsNoOpWhenBusy` test: rename it and assert that reorder **succeeds** when `IsBusy` is true:

```csharp
// Before (line 149-159):
[Fact]
public void MoveTask_IsNoOpWhenBusy()
{
    var viewModel = new MainWindowViewModel { IsBusy = true };
    viewModel.Tasks.Add(new TaskRowViewModel(new("a", "/tmp/llm-tasks/a.md", "/tmp/llm-tasks", false, [])));
    viewModel.Tasks.Add(new TaskRowViewModel(new("b", "/tmp/llm-tasks/b.md", "/tmp/llm-tasks", false, [])));

    viewModel.MoveTask(0, 1);

    Assert.Equal(["a", "b"], viewModel.Tasks.Select(t => t.Id));
}

// After:
[Fact]
public void MoveTask_ReordersWhenBusy()
{
    var viewModel = new MainWindowViewModel { IsBusy = true };
    viewModel.Tasks.Add(new TaskRowViewModel(new("a", "/tmp/llm-tasks/a.md", "/tmp/llm-tasks", false, [])));
    viewModel.Tasks.Add(new TaskRowViewModel(new("b", "/tmp/llm-tasks/b.md", "/tmp/llm-tasks", false, [])));

    viewModel.MoveTask(0, 1);

    Assert.Equal(["b", "a"], viewModel.Tasks.Select(t => t.Id));
}
```

---

### Safety invariants preserved

| Guard | Still gated on `IsBusy`? | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| `CanRunSelected` / `CanDrain` | ✅ Yes | Prevents starting a second run concurrently |
| `CanMarkSelectedTaskDone` | ✅ Yes | Prevents archive mutations during execution |
| `CanRefresh` | ✅ Yes | Prevents list rebuild during execution (though the drain's own reload is inside `RunBusyAsync` already) |
| `CanAddAttachments` | ✅ Yes | Prevents file mutations during execution |
| **`ReorderEnabled` / `MoveTask`** | ❌ **No** (relaxed) | Reorder is visual-only; drain/code snapsnot the order; persistence survives reload |

